Vesta is an independent client for hestia (https://github.com/mateusz-klatt/hestia).
It communicates with a hestia server only over hestia's network HTTP/OpenAPI API
and contains none of hestia's source. hestia is licensed AGPL-3.0; that license
binds whoever operates a hestia server, not this separate client, so Vesta is free
to be Apache-2.0.

Swift API types and client are generated at build time by Apache-2.0 licensed
apple/swift-openapi-generator from Vesta/openapi.json (a pinned copy of hestia's
emitted OpenAPI document). The generated output is the app's own work product.
